<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum75/HTML/000135.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#400000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#400000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Kaeden_ky</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">There seems to be a lack of rogue skills.  SO i would love to know if there is a buzz on adding more.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Stormwaltz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">*cough* I'm a designer, so I'm not really "buzz," but I can give a definite answer...<P>Sorry, Kaeden. Truly effective rogue skills would require new code, and that has to wait until v1.1, which only happens if 1.0 sells well. There's really no way to play a true rogue in AC, which is why the Rogue template was renamed Vagabond. Vagabond said "bum" to me, but I was outvoted...<P>Long ago, there were plans for stealth rolls to see/hear other players, or to be detected by monsters. Both could be surprise-attacked/backstabbed. Far away in a happier land, the designers dreamed of skills that allowed would-be thieves to scale the walls of guarded houses, and enter the second floor windows.<P>Know those big upper stabbing limbs on the Olthoi? Originally, those were climbing arms, and Olthoi hives were to be huge, vertical tubes under "ant hill" surface mounds, with tunnels leading off from the core. Unfortunately, the code as it was would allow a creature/player to start climbing even with no wall present - imagine a two-ton Olthoi noble scaling the air in front of you.<P>Why didn't it simply get fixed? Not enough dev time. If AC was the game everyone had dreamed it would be when they started, nothing else could have held a candle to it until 2005. Seriously - I just got a peek at the old-old 1996/7 design docs. They're amazing.<P>- Chris (frustrated Bum... Er, "Vagabond")<P>------------------<BR>** Turbine Entertainment Software doesn't know I said this. Shh.<p>[This message has been edited by Stormwaltz (edited September 20, 1999).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Havoc_3D</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">I do wanna add that i have had a Bum,they are utterly useless,without any type of theif skils they are just shop keepers,honestly.  Oh Wow,they can apprase stuff,that's realy useful in a fight,they can't fight worth crap  and have no useful skills, they can pick locks,at fist i though,ok,not that would be useful,then i got into the game and found NOTHING was locked,all chests are open already,and there are no locked doors that i have come across. so what's teh Deal Turbine,why even have a "Vegabond"<P>              -Havoc_3D</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Joe Napalm</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans"><BR>Actually, there are a LOT of locked doors and chests. I've been saving up my precious skill points for level after level to get lockpicking...<P>Of course, this doesn't make the Vagabond any more viable, since anyone can choose to learn to pick locks - which I rather like, actually.<P>Look at it this way:<P>Pickpocket skills don't really have a place in AC - people couldn't even tolerate looting so stealing is right out.<P>Stealth doesn't have a place because the AI is too simple...besides, there aren't any situations that I've come across in AC where being sneaky would even be particularly useful.<P>So, basically, AC wasn't designed with thief-style characters in mind, and Vagabonds (previously called Rogues) were included as a vestigal template from back when the design included things like climbing walls and such.<P>I'd say if you don't have any interest in playing anything but a sneaky thief, you're out of luck in AC.<P>-Jn-</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Aspasia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">As For The Rogue/Vagabond Character... I've Made An Attempt To Get Into It. The Only Things I Could Think Of To Do Were To Beg From People (Almost Like Pickpocketing, Isn't It? If You get Annoying Enough People Give You Something To Shut You Up) Then There Was Looting But That's Gone Now... There's The Lockpicking, Which Came In Handy When You Followed The "Big Guys" Into The Dungeons And Found Yourself A Chest While They Were Getting Butchered... And If You Do Things Like Appraise/ID People's Items And "Forget" To Give Them Back... That Can Be Considered Pickpocketing, Also. But Nobody Would Do That, Would They?  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"> Also, Using Bow/Crossbow Skills Made You Feel About Right As A "Rogue" So I Recommend That. It's All About The Roll... Skills Can Be Adapted To. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
